// @check
// @error cannot infer a type for `_m`
// DIAGNOSTIC (B6a, BUG 3): `Map()` takes its concrete type from context (the
// binding annotation). With no annotation the type can't be pinned, so the
// compiler reports a clear, actionable "cannot infer … annotate" error instead
// of dying with a generic "Unhandled Unknown type". This is the SAME unified
// diagnostic raised for any un-inferable binding (an empty `[]`, a `Set()`), and
// it fires at the declaration during the type/parse gate — before codegen. The
// lint pass (which would otherwise emit an intentionally-unused hint for `_m`) is
// suppressed once the file has an error-severity diagnostic, so no hint here.
let _m = Map()
